00:01:17.660 --> 00:01:27.560
And therefore, we have to likely look for targets and pathways that are uniquely important at that stage and at the pre-cancerous stage.

00:01:27.780 --> 00:01:47.640
And we have put a lot of effort, both in mouse genetic models, longitudinal models of the transformation process that we have developed over the last 15 plus years, as well as studies of sorted pre-leukemic stem cells from patients, and we've identified really a number of targets and validated targets and developed drugs over the years.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:53.440
And I would just say, they broadly, the most common targets fall into two categories.

00:01:53.920 --> 00:02:15.500
One, you see here on the left at the bottom, are targets that mediate cytokine stimuli, selection stimuli that act on the cells, including, for instance, IL-1 RAP, IL-8 CXCR2, PAK1, S100A8A9, we've heard about earlier today, and there's some others.

00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:17.500
And then the second one, and it's on the right, are triggers.

00:02:17.640 --> 00:02:23.200
And then the third one is the transcriptional regulators, and those I want to focus on first.

00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:29.140
And again, I had shown you this morning how important transcriptional variability is.

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:30.500
So how do you target this?

00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:41.800
So one example, and we reported this in a bunch of papers in the last few years, is MDM4, obviously a canonical inhibitor of the transcription factor TP53.

00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:47.620
It is selectively elevated in pre-leukemic stem cells in AML versus age-matched healthy coronary.

00:02:47.620 --> 00:02:54.300
It's somewhat unique to AML, doesn't really go up in most other tumor types.

00:02:54.540 --> 00:03:11.460
And what we found at that time was really, if you look at the MDS patients, the MDM4 expression levels or MDMX really very strongly correlates with the transformation or the likelihood of transformation of MDS to AML.

00:03:11.460 --> 00:03:17.460
And we've also been successful in contributing to some drug testing.

00:03:17.620 --> 00:03:19.180
And we've also been successful in contributing to some drug development in that area.

00:03:19.340 --> 00:03:25.160
So this is a stapled peptide approach of a dual MDM4, MDM2 inhibitor we tested a few years ago.

00:03:25.660 --> 00:03:36.560
And I'm just showing you this to say, even in very aggressive preclinical models of this transition, and you can see this on the survival graph.

00:03:36.560 --> 00:03:41.600
So in the untreated group, very aggressive models, all animals are dead within 50 days.

00:03:43.520 --> 00:03:47.440
This pre-emptive treatment and reactivating P53.

00:03:47.620 --> 00:03:53.860
